createAdjNode

public RSDepTreeNode createAdjNode(java.lang.String adj,
                                   java.lang.String pos,
                                   java.lang.String rel,
                                   boolean morph)
Creates a node for an adjective with the correct morph tag. Furthermore if the String is a verb, the correct tense of the verb is selected first. An example is the word 'tegenstribbelen', this is first changed into 'tegenstribbelend' and finally this can be inflected into 'tegenstribbelende' in the Morphology class.

createPronNode

Creates a node for a pronoun

createNullNode

public RSDepTreeNode createNullNode(java.lang.String rel)
Creates a node in which all strings are initialized to "" Can be used if a word is not stored in the lexicon in which case the word is simply removed and the program is executed normally (instead of a nullpointerexception)
